obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (20876)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20876&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the`
  line `Suppression of Unlawful Acts Against Safety of Maritime Navigation and Fixed Platforms on Continental`
  line `Shelf Act, 2002.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India including the limit of the territorial waters, the continental shelf,`
  line `the exclusive economic zone or any other maritime zone of India within the meaning of section 2 of the`
  line `Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive Economic Zone and other Maritime Zones Act, 1976`
  line `(80 of 1976).`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided, it shall apply--`
  line
  line `(a) to any offence under section 3 committed outside India by any person;`
  line
  line `(b) to a ship, if that ship is navigating or scheduled to navigate into, through or from waters`
  line `beyond the outer limits of the territorial waters of India, or the lateral limits of its territorial waters`
  line `with adjacent States;`
  line
  line `(c) when the offence is committed on board a ship in the territorial waters of India or against a`
  line `fixed platform located on the Continental Shelf of India.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), this Act shall apply only to offences`
  line `committed by an offender or alleged offender,--`
  line
  line `(a) when such an offender is found in the territory of a Convention State;`
  line
  line `(b) when such an offender is found in the territory of a Protocol State in whose internal water or`
  line `territorial waters or continental shelf the fixed platform is located; or`
  line
  line `(c) when such an offender is found in the territory of a State other than the State referred to in`
  line `clause (a) or clause (b).`
  line
  line `(5) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 1st February, 2003, vide notification No. S.O. 115(E), dated 30th, January, 2003, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part`
  line `II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (20877)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20877&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Code" means the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(b) "Continental Shelf of India" shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Territorial Waters,`
  line `Continental Shelf, Exclusive Economic Zone and other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976);`
  line
  line `(c) "Convention" means the Convention for the Suppression of Unlawful Acts Against the Safety`
  line `of Maritime Navigation, signed at Rome on the10th day of March, 1988 as amended from time to`
  line time;
  line
  line `(d) "Convention State" means a State Party to the Convention;`
  line
  line `(e) "fixed platform" means an artificial island, installation or structure permanently attached to`
  line `the seabed for the purpose of exploration for, or exploitation of resources or for other economic`
  line purposes;
  line
  line `(f) "Protocol" means the Protocol for the Suppression of Unlawful Acts Against the Safety of`
  line `Fixed Platforms Located on the Continental Shelf adopted at Rome on the 10th day of March,1988 as`
  line `amended from time to time;`
  line
  line `(g) "Protocol State" means a State Party to the Protocol;`
  line
  line `(h) "ship" means a vessel of any type whatsoever not permanently attached to the seabed and`
  line `includes dynamically supported craft, submersibles, or any other floating craft.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (20878)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Offences against ship, fixed platform, cargo of a ship, maritime navigational facilities, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20878&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever unlawfully and intentionally--`
  line
  line `(a) commits an act of violence against a person on board a fixed platform or a ship which is likely`
  line `to endanger the safety of the fixed platform or, as the case may be, safe navigation of the ship shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(b) destroys a fixed platform or a ship or causes damage to a fixed platform or a ship or cargo of`
  line `the ship in such manner which is likely to endanger the safety of such platform or safe navigation of`
  line `such ship shall be punished with imprisonment for life;`
  line
  line `(c) seizes or exercises control over a fixed platform or a ship by force or threatens or in any other`
  line `form intimidates shall be punished with imprisonment for life;`
  line
  line `(d) places or causes to be placed on a fixed platform or a ship, by any means whatsoever, a device`
  line `or substance which is likely to destroy that fixed platform or that ship or cause damage to that fixed`
  line `platform or that ship or its cargo which endangers o is likely to endanger that fixed platform or the`
  line `safe navigation of that ship shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `fourteen years;`
  line
  line `(e) destroys or damages maritime navigational facilities or interferes with their operation if such`
  line `act is likely to endanger the safe navigation of a ship shall be punished with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to fourteen years;`
  line
  line `(f) communicates information which he knows to be false thereby endangering the safe`
  line `navigation of a ship shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen`
  line `years and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line
  line `(g) in the course of commission of or in attempt to commit, any of the offences specified in`
  line `clauses (a) to (d) in connection with a fixed platform or clauses (a) to (f) in connection with a ship--`
  line
  line `(i) causes death to any person shall be punished with death;`
  line
  line `(ii) causes grievous hurt to any person shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to fourteen years;`
  line
  line `(iii) causes injury to any person shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years;`
  line
  line `(iv) seizes or threatens a person shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to ten years; and`
  line
  line `(v) threatens to endanger a ship or a fixed platform shall be punished with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to two years.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever attempts to commit, or abets the commission of, an offence punishable under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be deemed to have committed such offence and shall be punished with the`
  line `punishment provided for such offence.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever unlawfully or intentionally threatens a person to compel that person to do or refrain from`
  line `doing any act or to commit any offence specified in clause (a), clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1),`
  line `if such threat is likely to endanger the safe navigation of a ship or safety of a fixed platform shall be`
  line `punished with the punishment provided for such offence.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any act referred to in sub-section (1) is committed,--`
  line
  line `(a) against or on board--`
  line
  line `(i) an Indian ship at the time of commission of the offence; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any ship in the territory of India including its territorial waters;`
  line
  line `(b) by a stateless person,`
  line `such act shall be deemed to be an offence committed by such person for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this sub-section, the expression "stateless person" means a person whose habitual`
  line `residence is in India but he does not have nationality of any country.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an offence under sub-section (1) is committed and the person accused of or suspected of`
  line `the commission of such offence is present in the territory of India and is not extradited to any Convention`
  line `State or Protocol State, as the case may be, such person shall be dealt with in India in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) On being satisfied that the circumstances so warrant, the Central Government or any other`
  line `authority designated by it shall take the person referred to in sub-section (5) and present in the territory of`
  line `India into custody or take measures, in accordance with the law for the time being in force, to ensure his`
  line `presence in India for such time as is necessary to enable any criminal or extradition proceeding to be`
  line `instituted:`
  line
  line `Provided that when a person is taken into custody under this sub-section, it shall be necessary for the`
  line `Central Government or any other authority designated by it to notify the Government of any Convention`
  line `State or Protocol State which have also established jurisdiction over the offence committed or suspected`
  line `to have been committed by the person in custody.`
  line
  line `(7) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (8), where an offence under sub-section (1) is committed`
  line `outside India, the person committing such offence may be dealt with in respect thereof as if such offence`
  line `had been committed at any place within India at which he may be found.`
  line
  line `(8) No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this section which is committed`
  line `outside India unless--`
  line
  line `(a) such offence is committed on a fixed platform or on board a ship flying the Indian flag at the`
  line `time the offence is committed;`
  line
  line `(b) such offence is committed on board a ship which is for the time being chartered without crew`
  line `to a lessee who has his principal place of business, or where he has no such place of business, his`
  line `permanent residence, is in India; or`
  line
  line `(c) the alleged offender is a citizen of India or is on a fixed platform or on board a ship in relation`
  line `to which such offence is committed when it enters the territorial waters of India or is found in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (20879)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Conferment of powers of investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20879&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code,`
  line `for the purpose of this Act, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, confer on`
  line `any gazetted officer of the Coast Guard or any other gazetted officer of the Central Government powers`
  line `of arrest, investigation and prosecution exercisable by a police officer under the Code.`
  line
  line `(2) All officers of police and all officers of Government are hereby required and empowered to assist`
  line `the officer of the Central Government referred to in sub-section (1), in the execution of provisions of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `Explanation. - For the purpose of this section, officer of the Coast Guard means an officer as`
  line `defined in clause (q) of section 2 of the Coast Guard Act, 1978 (30 of 1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (20880)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Designated Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20880&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of providing for speedy trial, the State Government`
  line `shall, with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High Court, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify a Court of Session to be a Designated Court for such area or areas as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, a Designated Court shall, as far as practicable,`
  line `hold the trial on a day-to-day basis.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (20881)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Offence triable by Designated Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20881&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code,--`
  line
  line `(a) all offences under this Act shall be triable only by the Designated Court specified under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) where a person accused of or suspected of the commission of an offence under this Act is`
  line `forwarded to a Magistrate under sub-section (2) or sub-section (2A) of section 167 of the Code, such`
  line `Magistrate may authorise the detention of such person in such custody as he thinks fit for a period not`
  line `exceeding fifteen days in the whole where such Magistrate is a Judicial Magistrate and seven days in`
  line `the whole where such Magistrate is an Executive Magistrate:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such Magistrate considers,--`
  line
  line `(i) when such person is forwarded to him as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(ii) upon or at any time before the expiry of the period of detention authorised by him,`
  line `that the detention of such person is unnecessary, he shall order such person to be forwarded to the`
  line `Designated Court having the jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(c) the Designated Court may exercise, in relation to the person forwarded to it under clause (b),`
  line `the same power which a Magistrate having jurisdiction to try a case may exercise under section 167`
  line `of the Code, in relation to an accused person in such case who has been forwarded to him under that`
  line section;
  line
  line `(d) a Designated Court may, upon a perusal of a complaint made by an officer of the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government, as the case may be, authorised in this behalf, take cognizance`
  line `of that offence without the accused being committed to it for trial.`
  line
  line `(2) When trying an offence under this Act, a Designated Court may also try an offence other than an`
  line `offence under this Act, with which the accused may, under the Code, be charged at the same trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (20882)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Application of Code to proceedings before a Designated Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20882&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in`
  line `this Act, the provisions of the Code shall apply to the proceedings before a Designated Court and the`
  line `person conducting a prosecution before a Designated Court shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (20883)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Provision as to bail.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20883&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in the Code, no person accused of an offence`
  line `punishable under this Act shall, if in custody, be released on bail or on his own bond unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the Public Prosecutor has been given an opportunity to oppose the application for such`
  line `release; and`
  line
  line `(b) where the Public Prosecutor opposes the application, the Court is satisfied that there are`
  line `reasonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence and that he is not likely to`
  line `commit any offence while on bail.`
  line
  line `(2) The limitations on granting of bail specified in sub-section (1) are in addition to the limitations`
  line `under the Code or any other law for the time being in force on granting of bail.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to affect the special powers of the High Court`
  line `regarding bail under section 439 of the Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (20884)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Provisions as to extradition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20884&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The offences under section 3shall be deemed to have been`
  line `included as extraditable offences and provided for in all the extradition treaties made by India with`
  line `Convention States or Protocol States and which extend to, and are binding on, India on the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of the application of the Extradition Act, 1962(34 of 1962) to offences under this`
  line `Act, any ship registered in a Convention State or Protocol State shall, at any time while that ship is`
  line `plying, be deemed to be within the jurisdiction of that Convention State or Protocol State, whether or not`
  line `it is for the time being also within the jurisdiction of any other country.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (20885)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Contracting parties to Convention or Protocol.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20885&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, certify as to which are the Convention States or Protocol States and to what extent`
  line `such States have availed themselves of the provisions of the Convention or Protocol, as the case may be,`
  line `and any such notification shall be conclusive evidence of the matters certified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (20886)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to treat certain ships to be registered in Convention States.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20886&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `If the Central`
  line `Government is satisfied that the requirements of the Convention have been satisfied in relation to any`
  line `ship, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that such ship shall, for the purposes of this Act,`
  line `be deemed to be registered in such Convention State as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (20887)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Previous sanction necessary for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20887&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for an offence under this Act`
  line `shall be instituted except with the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (20888)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Presumptions as to offences under section 3.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733&sectionId=20888&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00006_200269_1517807324733
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `In a prosecution for an offence under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3, if it is proved--`
  line
  line `(a) that the arms, ammunition or explosives were recovered from the possession of the accused`
  line `and there is reason to believe that such arms, ammunition or explosives of similar nature were used in`
  line `the commission of such offence;`
  line
  line `(b) that there is evidence of use of force, threat of force or any other form of intimidation caused`
  line `to the crew or passengers in connection with the commission of such offence; or`
  line
  line `(c) that there is evidence of an intended threat of using bomb, fire, arms, ammunition, or`
  line `explosives or committing any form of violence against the crew, passengers or cargo of a ship or`
  line `fixed platform located on the Continental Shelf of India,`
  line `the Designated Court shall presume, unless the contrary is proved, that the accused had committed such`
  line offence.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
